1.  This command will create the Controller CA certificate and initialises
the PKI infrastructure to create the controller certificate and controller
private key.
     
    sudo ./mul-pki-cmd init

2.  This command will generate and install the Controller Certificate and Controller
private key to /etc/mul.

    sudo ./mul-pki-cmd req+sign+install ctl controller 


3.  Copy switch CA certificate to /etc/mul/ 

4.  Copy controller CA certificate from /etc/mul/pki/controllerca/cacert.pem
to the switch location.
